                        JOSEPH SELBY
                   (policeman, F 137). I produce a certificate—(Read: John Dillon, convicted, at Westminster, Aug., 1853, of stealing a watch; 
Confined four months)—I was present—the prisoner is the person.

104.
SAMUEL SHERVILL was again indicted
for a like offence. ( No evidence was offered.)
